jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-shapes-09-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-shapes-09-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-shapes-09-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-shapes-09-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-shapes-09-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-shapes-09-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-shapes-09-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-shapes-09-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-shapes-09-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><p>An alternative would be to use the other ports on the bottom of the flats. These are shown here plugged, and they’re intended for remote switches (like Shimano’s Di2 climber’s buttons and SRAM Blips), but I suspect for some frames, they’ll make a better option for brake hose exits.</p><p>We’ll see.</p><p>Until then, I’ll ride it like this, and that’s fine.</p><figure id=\"attachment_252286\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-252286\"><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar.jpg\" alt=\"Yuri hauswald rides the coefficient wave rr handlebars on gravel\" width=\"1200\" height=\"919\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-297x227.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-800x613.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-120x92.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-768x588.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-696x533.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-1068x818.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-548x420.jpg 548w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-80x60.jpg 80w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-297x227.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-800x613.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-120x92.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-768x588.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-696x533.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-1068x818.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-548x420.jpg 548w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Yuri-Hauswauld-coefficient-RR-wave-handlebar-80x60.jpg 80w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-252286\">Yuri Hauswald is a fan, and shows that the Wave RR might be equally good on a gravel bike, too.</figcaption></figure><p>First impressions are really good. Yes, I feel more aero. But more importantly, I feel much more comfortable.</p><p>It didn’t matter where I rested my hands, it felt good. I’m inclined to say it’s the most comfortable handlebar I’ve ever ridden, but I’d like to get the 44cm width in and log more miles and longer days before definitively stating something so bold.</p><p>Coefficient says the bars put your hands in the same position as with a normal bar, however I ended up running a 10mm shorter stem and it felt better.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02.jpg\" alt=\"coefficient wave rr aero road bike handlebar with light or gopro mount shown underneath\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-265x198.jpg 265w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/coefficient-RR-ergo-aero-road-bike-handlebar-on-bike-02-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><p>All those bends and angles do raise the question of safety. Coefficient says the bar uses Toray UD fibers throughout, and is tested to ISO standards for road and mountain biking. It feels solid, and seemed to damp road vibration quite well…which may be partly because the bars are further offset from the stem with that forward angle.</p><p>Retail is $399 and it comes with one computer mount, but options are available for 10 different GPS cycling computer brands.</p><p>There’s even a mount for a GoPro adapter underneath, which works great for lights.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.coefficient.cc/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Coefficient.cc</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"a9ea39fd27a609e1bbea4bfa3b319b5f44729e56d7f4f33e0390a03ac04513e7","category":"Cycling"}